text: The Frank F. Cranz House is a historic house in Nogales, Arizona. It was built in 1901-1907 for Franklin F. Cranz, who served as the mayor of Nogales from 1904 to 1906. With It was designed in the Queen Anne architectural style. It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since August 29, 1985. ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Santa Cruz County, Arizona Category:Queen Anne architecture in Arizona Category:Houses completed in 1907
title: Frank F. Cranz House
